defaultWhy did we want to ask them?
defaultWe felt that the Select Committee’s Enquiry 
defaultmust 
defaultbe informed by
default the voices and views of those who are working at the frontline with white working class 
defaultchildren and young people
default, as well as with their peers from ethnic minorities. All the organisations we support have a track record of working successfully to 
defaulteither
default s
defaultupport educational attainment
default of disadvantaged young people
default, or of 
defaultworking to re-engage them in education. They are well-placed to comment on any differences in challenges to educational attainment between white working class young people compared to those
default from ethnic minorities. More importantly, they are best placed to share their successful methods of engagement that convince some of the most excluded and disadvantaged young people to reconnect with education and employment. These methods should be studi
defaulted, and reflected upon by every head teacher in the country. 
